{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Chris Anderson: We're having a debate."},{"time":2000,"text":"The debate is over the proposition:"},{"time":4000,"text":"\"What the world needs now"},{"time":6000,"text":"is nuclear energy.\" True or false?"},{"time":9000,"text":"And before we have the debate,"},{"time":11000,"text":"I'd like to actually take a show of hands --"},{"time":13000,"text":"on balance, right now, are you for or against this?"},{"time":16000,"text":"So those who are \"yes,\" raise your hand. \"For.\""},{"time":20000,"text":"Okay, hands down."},{"time":22000,"text":"Those who are against, raise your hands."},{"time":25000,"text":"Okay, I'm reading that at about"},{"time":28000,"text":"75 to 25 in favor at the start."},{"time":31000,"text":"Which means we're going to take a vote at the end"},{"time":34000,"text":"and see how that shifts, if at all."},{"time":37000,"text":"So here's the format: They're going to have six minutes each,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and then after one little, quick exchange between them,"},{"time":42000,"text":"I want two people on each side of this debate in the audience"},{"time":44000,"text":"to have 30 seconds"},{"time":46000,"text":"to make one short, crisp, pungent, powerful point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"So, in favor of the proposition, possibly shockingly,"},{"time":53000,"text":"is one of, truly, the founders of the"},{"time":55000,"text":"environmental movement,"},{"time":57000,"text":"a long-standing TEDster, the founder of the Whole Earth Catalog,"},{"time":60000,"text":"someone we all know and love, Stewart Brand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63000,"text":"Stewart Brand: Whoa."},{"time":65000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":67000,"text":"The saying is that with climate, those who know the most"},{"time":69000,"text":"are the most worried."},{"time":71000,"text":"With nuclear, those who know the most"},{"time":73000,"text":"are the least worried."},{"time":75000,"text":"A classic example is James Hansen,"},{"time":77000,"text":"a NASA climatologist"},{"time":79000,"text":"pushing for 350 parts per million"},{"time":81000,"text":"carbon dioxide in the atmosphere."},{"time":83000,"text":"He came out with a wonderful book recently"},{"time":85000,"text":"called \"Storms of My Grandchildren.\""},{"time":87000,"text":"And Hansen is hard over for nuclear power,"},{"time":90000,"text":"as are most climatologists"},{"time":92000,"text":"who are engaging this issue seriously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"This is the design situation:"},{"time":97000,"text":"a planet that is facing climate change"},{"time":100000,"text":"and is now half urban."},{"time":103000,"text":"Look at the client base for this."},{"time":105000,"text":"Five out of six of us"},{"time":107000,"text":"live in the developing world."},{"time":109000,"text":"We are moving to cities. We are moving up in the world."},{"time":112000,"text":"And we are educating our kids,"},{"time":114000,"text":"having fewer kids,"},{"time":116000,"text":"basically good news all around."},{"time":118000,"text":"But we move to cities, toward the bright lights,"},{"time":120000,"text":"and one of the things that is there that we want, besides jobs,"},{"time":122000,"text":"is electricity."},{"time":124000,"text":"And if it isn't easily gotten, we'll go ahead and steal it."},{"time":127000,"text":"This is one of the most desired things"},{"time":129000,"text":"by poor people all over the world,"},{"time":131000,"text":"in the cities and in the countryside."},{"time":135000,"text":"Electricity for cities, at its best,"},{"time":137000,"text":"is what's called baseload electricity."},{"time":139000,"text":"That's where it is on"},{"time":141000,"text":"all the time."},{"time":143000,"text":"And so far there are only three major sources of that --"},{"time":146000,"text":"coal and gas, hydro-electric,"},{"time":148000,"text":"which in most places is maxed-out --"},{"time":150000,"text":"and nuclear."},{"time":152000,"text":"I would love to have something in the fourth place here,"},{"time":155000,"text":"but in terms of constant, clean,"},{"time":157000,"text":"scalable energy,"},{"time":159000,"text":"[solar] and wind and the other renewables"},{"time":161000,"text":"aren't there yet because they're inconstant."},{"time":163000,"text":"Nuclear is and has been for 40 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"Now, from an environmental standpoint,"},{"time":169000,"text":"the main thing you want to look at"},{"time":171000,"text":"is what happens to the waste from nuclear and from coal,"},{"time":174000,"text":"the two major sources of electricity."},{"time":178000,"text":"If all of your electricity in your lifetime came from nuclear,"},{"time":181000,"text":"the waste from that lifetime of electricity"},{"time":183000,"text":"would go in a Coke can --"},{"time":185000,"text":"a pretty heavy Coke can, about two pounds."},{"time":189000,"text":"But one day of coal"},{"time":192000,"text":"adds up to one hell of a lot"},{"time":194000,"text":"of carbon dioxide"},{"time":196000,"text":"in a normal one-gigawatt coal-fired plant."},{"time":201000,"text":"Then what happens to the waste?"},{"time":203000,"text":"The nuclear waste typically goes into"},{"time":205000,"text":"a dry cask storage"},{"time":207000,"text":"out back of the parking lot at the reactor site"},{"time":209000,"text":"because most places don't have underground storage yet."},{"time":211000,"text":"It's just as well, because it can stay where it is."},{"time":214000,"text":"While the carbon dioxide,"},{"time":216000,"text":"vast quantities of it, gigatons,"},{"time":219000,"text":"goes into the atmosphere"},{"time":221000,"text":"where we can't get it back -- yet --"},{"time":223000,"text":"and where it is causing the problems that we're most concerned about."},{"time":227000,"text":"So when you add up the greenhouse gases"},{"time":230000,"text":"in the lifetime of these various energy sources,"},{"time":233000,"text":"nuclear is down there with wind and hydro,"},{"time":236000,"text":"below solar and way below, obviously, all the fossil fuels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"Wind is wonderful; I love wind."},{"time":243000,"text":"I love being around these"},{"time":245000,"text":"big wind generators."},{"time":248000,"text":"But one of the things we're discovering is that"},{"time":250000,"text":"wind, like solar, is an actually relatively"},{"time":252000,"text":"dilute source of energy."},{"time":254000,"text":"And so it takes a very large footprint on the land,"},{"time":257000,"text":"a very large footprint in terms of materials,"},{"time":259000,"text":"five to 10 times what you'd use for nuclear,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and typically to get one gigawatt of electricity"},{"time":265000,"text":"is on the order of 250 square miles"},{"time":268000,"text":"of wind farm."},{"time":270000,"text":"In places like Denmark and Germany,"},{"time":273000,"text":"they've maxed out on wind already."},{"time":275000,"text":"They've run out of good sites."},{"time":277000,"text":"The power lines are getting overloaded."},{"time":280000,"text":"And you peak out."},{"time":282000,"text":"Likewise, with solar,"},{"time":284000,"text":"especially here in California,"},{"time":286000,"text":"we're discovering that the 80 solar farm"},{"time":288000,"text":"schemes that are going forward"},{"time":290000,"text":"want to basically bulldoze"},{"time":292000,"text":"1,000 square miles of southern California desert."},{"time":295000,"text":"Well, as an environmentalist, we would rather that didn't happen."},{"time":298000,"text":"It's okay on frapped-out agricultural land."},{"time":301000,"text":"Solar's wonderful on rooftops."},{"time":304000,"text":"But out in the landscape,"},{"time":306000,"text":"one gigawatt is on the order of 50 square miles"},{"time":309000,"text":"of bulldozed desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"When you add all these things up --"},{"time":313000,"text":"Saul Griffith did the numbers and figured out"},{"time":315000,"text":"what would it take"},{"time":317000,"text":"to get 13 clean"},{"time":319000,"text":"terawatts of energy"},{"time":322000,"text":"from wind, solar and biofuels,"},{"time":325000,"text":"and that area would be roughly the size of the United States,"},{"time":328000,"text":"an area he refers to as \"Renewistan.\""},{"time":332000,"text":"A guy who's added it up all this very well is David Mackay,"},{"time":335000,"text":"a physicist in England,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and in his wonderful book, \"Sustainable Energy,\" among other things,"},{"time":340000,"text":"he says, \"I'm not trying to be pro-nuclear. I'm just pro-arithmetic.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"In terms of weapons,"},{"time":349000,"text":"the best disarmament tool so far is nuclear energy."},{"time":352000,"text":"We have been taking down"},{"time":354000,"text":"the Russian warheads,"},{"time":356000,"text":"turning it into electricity."},{"time":358000,"text":"Ten percent of American electricity"},{"time":360000,"text":"comes from decommissioned warheads."},{"time":362000,"text":"We haven't even started the American stockpile."},{"time":366000,"text":"I think of most interest to a TED audience"},{"time":369000,"text":"would be the new generation of reactors"},{"time":371000,"text":"that are very small,"},{"time":373000,"text":"down around 10"},{"time":375000,"text":"to 125 megawatts."},{"time":377000,"text":"This is one from Toshiba."},{"time":379000,"text":"Here's one the Russians are already building that floats on a barge."},{"time":382000,"text":"And that would be very interesting in the developing world."},{"time":385000,"text":"Typically, these things are put in the ground."},{"time":387000,"text":"They're referred to as nuclear batteries."},{"time":389000,"text":"They're incredibly safe,"},{"time":391000,"text":"weapons proliferation-proof and all the rest of it."},{"time":393000,"text":"Here is a commercial version from New Mexico"},{"time":396000,"text":"called the Hyperion,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and another one from Oregon called NuScale."},{"time":401000,"text":"Babcock &amp; Wilcox that make nuclear reactors,"},{"time":403000,"text":"here's an integral fast reactor."},{"time":406000,"text":"Thorium reactor that Nathan Myhrvold's involved in."},{"time":409000,"text":"The governments of the world are going to have to decide"},{"time":411000,"text":"that coals need to be made expensive, and these will go ahead."},{"time":414000,"text":"And here's the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":422000,"text":"CA: Okay. Okay."},{"time":424000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":428000,"text":"So arguing against,"},{"time":430000,"text":"a man who's been at the nitty, gritty heart"},{"time":433000,"text":"of the energy debate and the climate change debate for years."},{"time":435000,"text":"In 2000, he discovered that soot"},{"time":438000,"text":"was probably the second leading cause of global warming, after CO2."},{"time":441000,"text":"His team have been making detailed calculations"},{"time":444000,"text":"of the relative impacts"},{"time":446000,"text":"of different energy sources."},{"time":448000,"text":"His first time at TED, possibly a disadvantage -- we shall see --"},{"time":451000,"text":"from Stanford,"},{"time":453000,"text":"Professor Mark Jacobson. Good luck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"Mark Jacobson: Thank you."},{"time":457000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":459000,"text":"So my premise here is that nuclear energy"},{"time":461000,"text":"puts out more carbon dioxide,"},{"time":463000,"text":"puts out more air pollutants,"},{"time":465000,"text":"enhances mortality more and takes longer to put up"},{"time":467000,"text":"than real renewable energy systems,"},{"time":469000,"text":"namely wind, solar,"},{"time":471000,"text":"geothermal power, hydro-tidal wave power."},{"time":474000,"text":"And it also enhances nuclear weapons proliferation."},{"time":477000,"text":"So let's start just by looking at the"},{"time":479000,"text":"CO2 emissions from the life cycle."},{"time":481000,"text":"CO2e emissions are equivalent emissions"},{"time":483000,"text":"of all the greenhouse gases and particles"},{"time":485000,"text":"that cause warming"},{"time":487000,"text":"and converted to CO2."},{"time":489000,"text":"And if you look, wind and concentrated solar"},{"time":491000,"text":"have the lowest CO2 emissions, if you look at the graph."},{"time":493000,"text":"Nuclear -- there are two bars here."},{"time":495000,"text":"One is a low estimate, and one is a high estimate."},{"time":497000,"text":"The low estimate is the nuclear energy industry"},{"time":499000,"text":"estimate of nuclear."},{"time":501000,"text":"The high is the average of 103"},{"time":503000,"text":"scientific, peer-reviewed studies."},{"time":505000,"text":"And this is just the"},{"time":507000,"text":"CO2 from the life cycle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509000,"text":"If we look at the delays,"},{"time":511000,"text":"it takes between 10 and 19 years"},{"time":513000,"text":"to put up a nuclear power plant"},{"time":515000,"text":"from planning to operation."},{"time":517000,"text":"This includes about three and a half to six years"},{"time":519000,"text":"for a site permit."},{"time":521000,"text":"and another two and a half to four years"},{"time":523000,"text":"for a construction permit and issue,"},{"time":525000,"text":"and then four to nine years for actual construction."},{"time":528000,"text":"And in China, right now,"},{"time":530000,"text":"they're putting up five gigawatts of nuclear."},{"time":532000,"text":"And the average, just for the construction time of these,"},{"time":535000,"text":"is 7.1 years"},{"time":537000,"text":"on top of any planning times."},{"time":539000,"text":"While you're waiting around for your nuclear,"},{"time":541000,"text":"you have to run the regular electric power grid,"},{"time":544000,"text":"which is mostly coal in the United States and around the world."},{"time":547000,"text":"And the chart here shows the difference between"},{"time":550000,"text":"the emissions from the regular grid,"},{"time":552000,"text":"resulting if you use nuclear, or anything else,"},{"time":555000,"text":"versus wind, CSP or photovoltaics."},{"time":558000,"text":"Wind takes about two to five years on average,"},{"time":561000,"text":"same as concentrated solar and photovoltaics."},{"time":563000,"text":"So the difference is the opportunity cost"},{"time":566000,"text":"of using nuclear versus wind, or something else."},{"time":569000,"text":"So if you add these two together, alone,"},{"time":571000,"text":"you can see a separation"},{"time":573000,"text":"that nuclear puts out at least nine to 17 times"},{"time":576000,"text":"more CO2 equivalent emissions than wind energy."},{"time":579000,"text":"And this doesn't even account"},{"time":581000,"text":"for the footprint on the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"If you look at the air pollution health effects,"},{"time":586000,"text":"this is the number of deaths per year in 2020"},{"time":588000,"text":"just from vehicle exhaust."},{"time":590000,"text":"Let's say we converted all the vehicles in the United States"},{"time":593000,"text":"to battery electric vehicles, hydrogen fuel cell vehicles"},{"time":596000,"text":"or flex fuel vehicles run on E85."},{"time":598000,"text":"Well, right now in the United States,"},{"time":600000,"text":"50 to 100,000 people die per year from air pollution,"},{"time":603000,"text":"and vehicles are about 25,000 of those."},{"time":606000,"text":"In 2020, the number will go down to 15,000"},{"time":608000,"text":"due to improvements."},{"time":610000,"text":"And so, on the right, you see gasoline emissions,"},{"time":612000,"text":"the death rates of 2020."},{"time":614000,"text":"If you go to corn or cellulosic ethanol,"},{"time":616000,"text":"you'd actually increase the death rate slightly."},{"time":618000,"text":"If you go to nuclear,"},{"time":620000,"text":"you do get a big reduction,"},{"time":622000,"text":"but it's not as much as with wind and concentrated solar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"Now if you consider the fact"},{"time":627000,"text":"that nuclear weapons proliferation"},{"time":630000,"text":"is associated with nuclear energy proliferation,"},{"time":632000,"text":"because we know for example,"},{"time":634000,"text":"India and Pakistan developed nuclear weapons secretly"},{"time":637000,"text":"by enriching uranium"},{"time":639000,"text":"in nuclear energy facilities."},{"time":641000,"text":"North Korea did that to some extent."},{"time":643000,"text":"Iran is doing that right now."},{"time":645000,"text":"And Venezuela would be doing it"},{"time":647000,"text":"if they started with their nuclear energy facilities."},{"time":650000,"text":"If you do a large scale expansion"},{"time":653000,"text":"of nuclear energy across the world,"},{"time":656000,"text":"and as a result there was just one"},{"time":658000,"text":"nuclear bomb created"},{"time":662000,"text":"that was used to destroy a city"},{"time":664000,"text":"such as Mumbai or some other big city, megacity,"},{"time":667000,"text":"the additional death rates due to this"},{"time":669000,"text":"averaged over 30 years and then scaled to the population of the U.S."},{"time":672000,"text":"would be this."},{"time":674000,"text":"So, do we need this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"The next thing is: What about the footprint? Stewart mentioned the footprint."},{"time":679000,"text":"Actually, the footprint on the ground for wind"},{"time":681000,"text":"is by far the smallest of any energy source in the world."},{"time":684000,"text":"That, because the footprint, as you can see,"},{"time":686000,"text":"is just the pole touching the ground."},{"time":688000,"text":"And you can power the entire U.S. vehicle fleet"},{"time":690000,"text":"with 73,000 to 145,000"},{"time":693000,"text":"five-megawatt wind turbines."},{"time":695000,"text":"That would take between one and three square kilometers"},{"time":698000,"text":"of footprint on the ground, entirely."},{"time":700000,"text":"The spacing is something else."},{"time":702000,"text":"That's the footprint that is always being confused."},{"time":704000,"text":"People confuse footprint with spacing."},{"time":706000,"text":"As you can see from these pictures,"},{"time":708000,"text":"the spacing between can be used for multiple purposes"},{"time":711000,"text":"including agricultural land,"},{"time":713000,"text":"range land or open space."},{"time":715000,"text":"Over the ocean, it's not even land."},{"time":717000,"text":"Now if we look at nuclear -- (Laughter)"},{"time":720000,"text":"With nuclear, what do we have?"},{"time":722000,"text":"We have facilities around there. You also have a buffer zone"},{"time":724000,"text":"that's 17 square kilometers."},{"time":726000,"text":"And you have the uranium mining"},{"time":728000,"text":"that you have to deal with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"Now if we go to the area,"},{"time":732000,"text":"lots is worse than nuclear or wind."},{"time":735000,"text":"For example, cellulosic ethanol, to power the entire U.S. vehicle fleet,"},{"time":738000,"text":"this is how much land you would need."},{"time":740000,"text":"That's cellulosic, second generation"},{"time":742000,"text":"biofuels from prairie grass."},{"time":744000,"text":"Here's corn ethanol. It's smaller."},{"time":746000,"text":"This is based on ranges from data,"},{"time":749000,"text":"but if you look at nuclear,"},{"time":751000,"text":"it would be the size of Rhode Island to power the U.S. vehicle fleet."},{"time":754000,"text":"For wind, there's a larger area,"},{"time":756000,"text":"but much smaller footprint."},{"time":758000,"text":"And of course, with wind,"},{"time":760000,"text":"you could put it all over the East Coast,"},{"time":762000,"text":"offshore theoretically, or you can split it up."},{"time":764000,"text":"And now, if you go back to"},{"time":766000,"text":"looking at geothermal, it's even smaller than both,"},{"time":769000,"text":"and solar is slightly larger than the nuclear spacing,"},{"time":772000,"text":"but it's still pretty small."},{"time":774000,"text":"And this is to power the entire U.S. vehicle fleet."},{"time":776000,"text":"To power the entire world with 50 percent wind,"},{"time":779000,"text":"you would need about one percent of world land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782000,"text":"Matching the reliability, base load is actually irrelevant."},{"time":784000,"text":"We want to match the hour-by-hour power supply."},{"time":787000,"text":"You can do that by combining renewables."},{"time":789000,"text":"This is from real data in California,"},{"time":791000,"text":"looking at wind data and solar data."},{"time":794000,"text":"And it considers just using existing hydro"},{"time":797000,"text":"to match the hour-by-hour power demand."},{"time":799000,"text":"Here are the world wind resources."},{"time":801000,"text":"There's five to 10 times more wind available worldwide"},{"time":803000,"text":"than we need for all the world."},{"time":805000,"text":"So then here's the final ranking."},{"time":807000,"text":"And one last slide I just want to show. This is the choice:"},{"time":810000,"text":"You can either have wind or nuclear."},{"time":812000,"text":"If you use wind,"},{"time":814000,"text":"you guarantee ice will last."},{"time":816000,"text":"Nuclear, the time lag alone"},{"time":818000,"text":"will allow the Arctic to melt and other places to melt more."},{"time":821000,"text":"And we can guarantee a clean, blue sky"},{"time":824000,"text":"or an uncertain future with nuclear power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":835000,"text":"CA: All right."},{"time":837000,"text":"So while they're having their comebacks on each other --"},{"time":839000,"text":"and yours is slightly short because you slightly overran --"},{"time":841000,"text":"I need two people from either side."},{"time":843000,"text":"So if you're for this,"},{"time":845000,"text":"if you're for nuclear power, put up two hands."},{"time":848000,"text":"If you're against, put up one."},{"time":850000,"text":"And I want two of each for the mics."},{"time":852000,"text":"Now then, you guys have --"},{"time":854000,"text":"you have a minute comeback on him"},{"time":857000,"text":"to pick up a point he said, challenge it,"},{"time":859000,"text":"whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863000,"text":"SB: I think a point of difference we're having, Mark,"},{"time":865000,"text":"has to do with weapons"},{"time":868000,"text":"and energy."},{"time":870000,"text":"These diagrams that show that nuclear is somehow"},{"time":872000,"text":"putting out a lot of greenhouse gases --"},{"time":874000,"text":"a lot of those studies include, \"Well of course war will be inevitable"},{"time":877000,"text":"and therefore we'll have cities burning and stuff like that,\""},{"time":879000,"text":"which is kind of finessing it"},{"time":881000,"text":"a little bit, I think."},{"time":884000,"text":"The reality is that there's, what,"},{"time":886000,"text":"21 nations that have nuclear power?"},{"time":889000,"text":"Of those, seven have nuclear weapons."},{"time":891000,"text":"In every case, they got the weapons"},{"time":893000,"text":"before they got the nuclear power."},{"time":896000,"text":"There are two nations, North Korea and Israel,"},{"time":898000,"text":"that have nuclear weapons"},{"time":900000,"text":"and don't have nuclear power at all."},{"time":902000,"text":"The places that we would most like to have"},{"time":905000,"text":"really clean energy occur"},{"time":907000,"text":"are China, India, Europe, North America,"},{"time":910000,"text":"all of which have sorted out their situation"},{"time":913000,"text":"in relation to nuclear weapons."},{"time":915000,"text":"So that leaves a couple of places like Iran,"},{"time":917000,"text":"maybe Venezuela,"},{"time":919000,"text":"that you would like to have very close"},{"time":922000,"text":"surveillance of anything"},{"time":924000,"text":"that goes on with fissile stuff."},{"time":926000,"text":"Pushing ahead with nuclear power will mean we"},{"time":928000,"text":"really know where all of the fissile material is,"},{"time":930000,"text":"and we can move toward"},{"time":932000,"text":"zero weapons left, once we know all that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935000,"text":"CA: Mark,"},{"time":937000,"text":"30 seconds, either on that or on anything Stewart said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940000,"text":"MJ: Well we know India and Pakistan had nuclear energy first,"},{"time":943000,"text":"and then they developed nuclear weapons secretly in the factories."},{"time":946000,"text":"So the other thing is, we don't need nuclear energy."},{"time":949000,"text":"There's plenty of solar and wind."},{"time":951000,"text":"You can make it reliable, as I showed with that diagram."},{"time":953000,"text":"That's from real data."},{"time":955000,"text":"And this is an ongoing research. This is not rocket science."},{"time":957000,"text":"Solving the world's problems can be done,"},{"time":960000,"text":"if you really put your mind to it and use clean, renewable energy."},{"time":963000,"text":"There's absolutely no need for nuclear power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":969000,"text":"CA: We need someone for."},{"time":971000,"text":"Rod Beckstrom: Thank you Chris. I'm Rod Beckstrom, CEO of ICANN."},{"time":974000,"text":"I've been involved in global warming policy"},{"time":976000,"text":"since 1994,"},{"time":978000,"text":"when I joined the board of Environmental Defense Fund"},{"time":980000,"text":"that was one of the crafters of the Kyoto Protocol."},{"time":983000,"text":"And I want to support Stewart Brand's position."},{"time":985000,"text":"I've come around in the last 10 years."},{"time":987000,"text":"I used to be against nuclear power."},{"time":989000,"text":"I'm now supporting Stewart's position,"},{"time":991000,"text":"softly, from a risk-management standpoint,"},{"time":993000,"text":"agreeing that"},{"time":995000,"text":"the risks of overheating the planet"},{"time":997000,"text":"outweigh the risk of nuclear incident,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"which certainly is possible and is a very real problem."},{"time":1003000,"text":"However, I think there may be a win-win solution here"},{"time":1005000,"text":"where both parties can win this debate,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"and that is, we face a situation"},{"time":1010000,"text":"where it's carbon caps on this planet"},{"time":1012000,"text":"or die."},{"time":1014000,"text":"And in the United States Senate,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"we need bipartisan support --"},{"time":1018000,"text":"only one or two votes are needed --"},{"time":1020000,"text":"to move global warming through the Senate,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"and this room can help."},{"time":1024000,"text":"So if we get that through, then Mark will solve these problems. Thanks Chris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027000,"text":"CA: Thank you Rod Beckstrom. Against."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"David Fanton: Hi, I'm David Fanton. I just want to say a couple quick things."},{"time":1032000,"text":"The first is: be aware of the propaganda."},{"time":1035000,"text":"The propaganda from the industry"},{"time":1037000,"text":"has been very, very strong."},{"time":1039000,"text":"And we have not had"},{"time":1041000,"text":"the other side of the argument fully aired"},{"time":1044000,"text":"so that people can draw their own conclusions."},{"time":1046000,"text":"Be very aware of the propaganda."},{"time":1048000,"text":"Secondly, think about this."},{"time":1050000,"text":"If we build all these nuclear power plants,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"all that waste"},{"time":1054000,"text":"is going to be on hundreds, if not thousands,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"of trucks and trains,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"moving through this country every day."},{"time":1060000,"text":"Tell me they're not going to have accidents."},{"time":1063000,"text":"Tell me that those accidents aren't going to"},{"time":1066000,"text":"put material into the environment"},{"time":1069000,"text":"that is poisonous for hundreds of thousands of years."},{"time":1071000,"text":"And then tell me that each and every one of those trucks and trains"},{"time":1074000,"text":"isn't a potential terrorist target."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076000,"text":"CA: Thank you."},{"time":1079000,"text":"For."},{"time":1081000,"text":"Anyone else for? Go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1084000,"text":"Alex: Hi, I'm Alex. I just wanted to say,"},{"time":1086000,"text":"I'm, first of all, renewable energy's biggest fan."},{"time":1088000,"text":"I've got solar PV on my roof."},{"time":1090000,"text":"I've got a hydro conversion"},{"time":1092000,"text":"at a watermill that I own."},{"time":1094000,"text":"And I'm, you know, very much \"pro\" that kind of stuff."},{"time":1097000,"text":"However, there's a basic arithmetic problem here."},{"time":1100000,"text":"The capability of"},{"time":1102000,"text":"the sun shining, the wind blowing and the rain falling,"},{"time":1105000,"text":"simply isn't enough to add up."},{"time":1107000,"text":"So if we want to keep the lights on,"},{"time":1109000,"text":"we actually need a solution"},{"time":1111000,"text":"which is going to keep generating all of the time."},{"time":1114000,"text":"I campaigned against nuclear weapons in the '80s,"},{"time":1117000,"text":"and I continue to do so now."},{"time":1119000,"text":"But we've got an opportunity"},{"time":1121000,"text":"to recycle them into something more useful"},{"time":1123000,"text":"that enables us to get energy all of the time."},{"time":1126000,"text":"And, ultimately, the arithmetic problem isn't going to go away."},{"time":1129000,"text":"We're not going to get enough energy from renewables alone."},{"time":1132000,"text":"We need a solution that generates all of the time."},{"time":1134000,"text":"If we're going to keep the lights on,"},{"time":1136000,"text":"nuclear is that solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1138000,"text":"CA: Thank you."},{"time":1141000,"text":"Anyone else against?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143000,"text":"Man: The last person who was in favor made the premise"},{"time":1145000,"text":"that we don't have enough"},{"time":1147000,"text":"alternative renewable resources."},{"time":1150000,"text":"And our \"against\" proponent up here"},{"time":1152000,"text":"made it very clear that we actually do."},{"time":1154000,"text":"And so the fallacy"},{"time":1156000,"text":"that we need this resource"},{"time":1158000,"text":"and we can actually make it in a time frame"},{"time":1160000,"text":"that is meaningful is not possible."},{"time":1162000,"text":"I will also add one other thing."},{"time":1164000,"text":"Ray Kurzweil and all the other talks --"},{"time":1166000,"text":"we know that the stick is going up exponentially."},{"time":1168000,"text":"So you can't look at state-of-the-art technologies in renewables"},{"time":1171000,"text":"and say, \"That's all we have.\""},{"time":1173000,"text":"Because five years from now, it will blow you away"},{"time":1175000,"text":"what we'll actually have as alternatives"},{"time":1177000,"text":"to this horrible, disastrous nuclear power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1179000,"text":"CA: Point well made. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1181000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184000,"text":"So each of you has really just a couple sentences --"},{"time":1186000,"text":"30 seconds each"},{"time":1188000,"text":"to sum up."},{"time":1191000,"text":"Your final pitch, Stewart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1193000,"text":"SB: I loved your \"It all balances out\" chart"},{"time":1196000,"text":"that you had there."},{"time":1198000,"text":"It was a sunny day and a windy night."},{"time":1201000,"text":"And just now in England"},{"time":1203000,"text":"they had a cold spell."},{"time":1205000,"text":"All of the wind in the entire country"},{"time":1207000,"text":"shut down for a week."},{"time":1209000,"text":"None of those things were stirring."},{"time":1211000,"text":"And as usual, they had to buy nuclear power from France."},{"time":1213000,"text":"Two gigawatts comes through the Chunnel."},{"time":1215000,"text":"This keeps happening."},{"time":1217000,"text":"I used to worry about the 10,000 year factor."},{"time":1221000,"text":"And the fact is, we're going to use the nuclear waste we have for fuel"},{"time":1224000,"text":"in the fourth generation of reactors that are coming along."},{"time":1227000,"text":"And especially the small reactors need to go forward."},{"time":1230000,"text":"I heard from Nathan Myhrvold -- and I think here's the action point --"},{"time":1233000,"text":"it'll take an act of Congress"},{"time":1235000,"text":"to make the Nuclear Regulatory Commission"},{"time":1237000,"text":"start moving quickly on these small reactors,"},{"time":1239000,"text":"which we need very much, here and in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1243000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1249000,"text":"MJ: So we've analyzed the hour-by-hour"},{"time":1251000,"text":"power demand and supply,"},{"time":1253000,"text":"looking at solar, wind, using data for California."},{"time":1256000,"text":"And you can match that demand, hour-by-hour,"},{"time":1259000,"text":"for the whole year almost."},{"time":1261000,"text":"Now, with regard to the resources,"},{"time":1263000,"text":"we've developed the first wind map of the world,"},{"time":1265000,"text":"from data alone, at 80 meters."},{"time":1267000,"text":"We know what the wind resources are. You can cover 15 percent."},{"time":1270000,"text":"Fifteen percent of the entire U.S."},{"time":1272000,"text":"has wind at fast enough speeds to be cost-competitive."},{"time":1275000,"text":"And there's much more solar than there is wind."},{"time":1277000,"text":"There's plenty of resource. You can make it reliable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1280000,"text":"CA: Okay. So, thank you, Mark."},{"time":1283000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1287000,"text":"So if you were in Palm Springs ..."},{"time":1290000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1295000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1297000,"text":"Shameless. Shameless. Shameless."},{"time":1300000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1302000,"text":"So, people of the TED community,"},{"time":1305000,"text":"I put it to you that what the world needs now"},{"time":1307000,"text":"is nuclear energy."},{"time":1309000,"text":"All those in favor, raise your hands."},{"time":1312000,"text":"(Shouts)"},{"time":1315000,"text":"And all those against."},{"time":1318000,"text":"Ooooh."},{"time":1320000,"text":"Now that is -- my take on that ..."},{"time":1322000,"text":"Just put up ... Hands up, people who changed their minds during the debate,"},{"time":1325000,"text":"who voted differently."},{"time":1327000,"text":"Those of you who changed your mind"},{"time":1330000,"text":"in favor of \"for\""},{"time":1332000,"text":"put your hands up."},{"time":1334000,"text":"Okay. So here's the read on it."},{"time":1337000,"text":"Both people won supporters,"},{"time":1339000,"text":"but on my count,"},{"time":1342000,"text":"the mood of the TED community shifted"},{"time":1344000,"text":"from about 75 to 25"},{"time":1346000,"text":"to about 65 to 35"},{"time":1348000,"text":"in favor, in favor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1350000,"text":"You both won. I congratulate both of you."},{"time":1352000,"text":"Thank you for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1354000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}